					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-76799#post-4538990</guid>
				<title>Re: The real SCP 001</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-76799/scp-001#post-4538990</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Mon, 09 Mar 2020 15:52:00 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Nagiros</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>4665703</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I believe they're referring to <span class="printuser"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/jack-ike" >Jack Ike</a></span>'s <a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/code-name-the-truth">pseudo-proposal</a>.</p> <p>Canon doesn't really work like that; an author saying their article is the real 001 doesn't make it officially so. Choose for yourself which you believe are &quot;real&quot;, if you want to play that game, but there will never be anything official.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
